snippet.textDisplay:
Honestly for some reason the over-the-top humour from the 1st Madagascar did make me chuckle, in fact it still can do this day. I couldn't stand the granny maniac though, and she appears even more in Esacpe 2 Africa. Speaking of said sequel, the only thing I remember (other than the granny) is being sufficiently entertained.
... But then.
The 3d one. The abomination. "Polka dot afro" was so overdone that by the time I watched the movie I found myslef dreading the actual part. That main action scene with the interpol lady was decent enough in my opinion, not sure but I think I was amused.
And the stupud brain-dead bear bothered me, I think.
That's it. That's all I remember, other than thinking "why did they make this movie".

And the fact that I can't remember much from 2 and 3 says a lot.

So, all this to say -- even though I don't share the same awe and respect for the trilogy as IHE -- this video's humour, like all others from the channel, is on point.
I've been in bed for a week or more now (my stupid leg, no need for details), and haven't been in the mood for laughing, but this video did it.
So, thank you.

And the stupud brain-dead bear bothered me, I think. 
That's it. That's all I remember, other than thinking "why did they make this movie".

And the fact that I can't remember much from 2 and 3 says a lot.

So, all this to say -- even though I don't share the same awe and respect for the trilogy as IHE -- this video's  humour, like all others from the channel, is on point.
I've been in bed for a week or more now (my stupid leg, no need for details), and haven't been in the mood for laughing, but this video did it. 
So, thank you.
